.TH JTUTIL-SEED "1" "June 2026" "jtutil manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-seed \- Run jtcore repeatedly with different seeds
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs jtcore repeatedly with different \fB\-\-seed\fR values until one build passes or max\-retries is reached.
.SS "Options consumed by jtutil seed must appear before max-retries/core:"
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR n
Run up to n jtcore seed builds at the same time
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR=\fI\,n\/\fR
Same as \fB\-\-parallel\fR n
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR | \fB\-h\fR
Show this summary
.PP
After optional max\-retries is removed, the remaining arguments are passed to
jtcore. In parallel mode each jtcore run gets a distinct \fB\-\-seed\fR and \fB\-\-output\fR
folder. The Quartus build runs under <output>/build, and its console output is written to <output>/jtcore.log. Parallel
runs invoke jtcore with \fB\-\-nocopy\fR; as jobs finish, jtutil seed copies the best
RBF seen so far into the normal release/<target>/ folder. The default output
base is:
.IP
$JTROOT/cores/<core\-name>/seed
.PP
Create a jtseed.last file in the current folder to stop after the current batch.
.PP
Use "man jtutil\-seed" for full documentation.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil seed [flags] [max\-retries] <core> [jtcore options]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for seed
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR int
Run up to n jtcore seed builds at the same time (default 1)
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose
